  "text": "which bind to the MTSS1 3' untranslated region and reduce steady-state MTSS1 protein levels [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] To determine whether MTSS1 protein accumulation is sensitive to Atxn2 we examined the ATXN2 Q127 mouse model of SCA2 [CITATION_6] . We found reduced Mtss1 abundance (Fig 4A, S3 ) and increased cerebellar SFK activity in ATXN2 Q127 animals compared to wild type littermates (Fig 4B) .",
